
// This Hyperlambda code uses the [and] slot to evaluate multiple conditions. It checks if the [cascading] node exists and is not null using [exists] and [not-null]. Then, it verifies if the value of [cascading] is exactly true using [eq]. The [and] slot ensures all conditions must be true for the entire expression to evaluate to true.
and
   exists:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
   not-null:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
   eq
      get-value:x:@.arguments/*/cascading
      .:bool:true
